casting: ['Michael York', 'Malcolm McDowell', 'John Rhys-Davies', 'Billy West', 'Grey DeLisle', 'Phil LaMarr', 'Kath Soucie', 'Jeff Bergman', 'Greg Ellis', 'Jess Harnell', 'Richard McGonagle']

titre: Tyler Perry's Meet The Browns - The Play
synopsis: A funeral can be a time for laughter (and lessons) when the kooky Brown family gathers to bury Brown's 107-year-old father. It's a foot-stomping sound-stirring send-off and a great reminder--"Ain't nothin' like family, ain't nothin' like love!"
tagline: Good ol' Pop Brown lived to be 107 years old and he only left his family $400 to put him to rest.
casting: ['David Mann', 'Tamela Mann', 'Terrell Phillips', 'Terrell Carter', 'Trina Braxton', 'Tamika Scott', 'Euclid Gray', 'Joyce Williams']

synopsis: The true story of teen surfer Bethany Hamilton, who lost her arm in a shark attack and courageously overcame all odds to become a champion again, through her sheer determination and unwavering faith.
tagline: When you come back from a loss, beat the odds, and never say never, you find a champion.
